 5  # -------------------
 6  # Main
 7  # -------------------
 8  # https://chart-studio.plotly.com/~empet/13748/sparklines/#/code
 9  # https://omnipotent.net/jquery.sparkline/#s-about
10  # https://chart-studio.plotly.com/create/?fid=Dreamshot:8025#/
11 
12  # Libraries
13  import glob
14  import numpy as np
15  import pandas as pd
16  import plotly.express as px
17  import plotly.graph_objects as go
18 
19  from pandas.tseries.offsets import DateOffset
20  from plotly.subplots import make_subplots
21 
22  # Constants
23  colors = px.colors.sequential.Viridis_r
24  colors += px.colors.sequential.Viridis_r
25 
26  # -------------------
27  # Load data
28  # -------------------
29  # Define folder
30  folder = './data/weather-hmc-dataset/'
31 
32  # Load data
33  data = pd.concat([pd.read_csv(f) \
34      for f in glob.glob('%s/*.csv' % folder)])
35 
36  # Drop duplicates
37  data = data.drop_duplicates()
38  data['dates'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date time'])
39  data = data.set_index('dates')
40  data = data.drop(columns=['Name',
41                            'Date time',
42                            'Conditions'])
43 
44  # Show data
45  print("\nData:")
46  print(data)
47 
48 
49  # ----------------
50  # Visualize
51  # ----------------
52  # Create layout
53  layout = {
54    "font": {"family": "Georgia, serif"},
55    "title": "Weather Ho Chi Minh (missing units!)",
56    #"width": 500,
57    "height": 1000,
58    #"margin": {"t": 80},
59    "paper_bgcolor": 'rgba(0,0,0,0)',  # transparent
60    "plot_bgcolor": 'rgba(0,0,0,0)',  # transparent
61    #"autosize": False,
62    "hovermode": "closest",
63    "showlegend": False,
64  }
65 
66  # Create figure
67  fig = make_subplots(rows=data.shape[1], cols=1,
68                      shared_xaxes=True,
69                      subplot_titles=[t for t in data.columns])
70 
71  # Add traces
72  for i, column in enumerate(data.columns):
73      # Colors
74      c = colors[i]
75      x = data.index
76      y = data[column]
77 
78      # Add trace
79      fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=x, y=y,
80          name=column,
81          mode='lines', fill='tozeroy',
82          line=dict(color=c, width=0.5)),
83          row=i+1, col=1)
84 
85      # Update axes
86      fig.update_yaxes(title_text='', row=i+1, col=1)
87 
88  # Update layout
89  fig.update_layout(layout)
90 
91  # Show
92  #fig.show()
93  fig
